I don't disagree.

254
00:13:47,375 --> 00:13:52,583
But get used to it...
This is life, boys.

255
00:13:52,666 --> 00:13:54,250
Your life...

256
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:58,166
From now until we see
fit to cut you loose.

257
00:13:58,250 --> 00:13:59,458
Or at least...

258
00:13:59,541 --> 00:14:03,208
...until Wonderland
claims you for its own.

259
00:14:03,791 --> 00:14:05,791
You can't just
slice up anybody.

260
00:14:05,875 --> 00:14:07,041
We don't want
the newbies left with

261
00:14:07,125 --> 00:14:09,041
the impression that
this is a free-for-all.

262
00:14:09,125 --> 00:14:11,958
You didn't even go over
death row regulations.

263
00:14:12,041 --> 00:14:13,833
And what would've
been the point?

264
00:14:13,916 --> 00:14:16,000
Five-five-eight-zero
was the only short-timer

265
00:14:16,083 --> 00:14:17,291
in today's bunch...

266
00:14:17,375 --> 00:14:20,458
And his "accident" is
just around the corner.

267
00:14:20,541 --> 00:14:23,125
Unless the decision
has been rescinded?

268
00:14:23,208 --> 00:14:24,375
I... understand.

269
00:14:24,458 --> 00:14:26,208
He's the only
newcomer to death row

270
00:14:26,291 --> 00:14:28,625
out of the batch we received
this afternoon, but...

271
00:14:28,708 --> 00:14:31,708
[MAKINA] The "accident's"
a ridiculous precaution.

272
00:14:31,791 --> 00:14:35,791
He's just a kid.
It isn't like he'll last long.

273
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:39,208
So what are you so antsy about?

274
00:14:39,291 --> 00:14:40,500
[TAMAKI] Chief Warden,

275
00:14:40,583 --> 00:14:42,208
when you find a
beautifully wrapped present

276
00:14:42,291 --> 00:14:46,583
on, say, your vanity
table, what do you do?

277
00:14:46,666 --> 00:14:47,750
[MAKINA] I open it.

278
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:50,541
[TAMAKI]
Indeed, as would I.

279
00:14:52,875 --> 00:14:54,125
Wrapping be damned,

280
00:14:54,208 --> 00:14:57,500
I just want to get at
what I know is inside.

281
00:14:59,291 --> 00:15:02,250
[DRILLING SOUNDS]

282
00:15:07,791 --> 00:15:09,416
[GATES CREAK SHUT]

283
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:14,166
[GANTA BREATHES HEAVILY]

284
00:15:15,916 --> 00:15:20,791
[SPARKS SIZZLE]

285
00:15:31,541 --> 00:15:33,125
[CROWD MAN 1-A] Die!

286
00:15:33,208 --> 00:15:35,750
[CROWD YELLS]

287
00:15:40,708 --> 00:15:43,833
Somebody please just kill me.

288
00:15:52,250 --> 00:15:54,458
[GANTA THINKING] Mimi...

289
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:59,166
You want me to kill you?

290
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:02,916
I could do it
in one swing.

291
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,166
[GANTA YELLS]

292
00:16:05,250 --> 00:16:06,750
Or not, if you dodge me...

293
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:07,500
[GANTA] What?

294
00:16:07,583 --> 00:16:08,750
Silly boy!

295
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:09,666
[GANTA YELLS]

296
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:11,958
What the hell is
wrong with you?!

297
00:16:12,041 --> 00:16:13,875
I don't even know who you--

298
00:16:13,958 --> 00:16:14,833
[GANTA YELLS]

299
00:16:14,916 --> 00:16:16,083
Ah ha!

300
00:16:16,166 --> 00:16:17,916
Huh...?

301
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:21,541
That was a fib back there, huh?

302
00:16:21,625 --> 00:16:24,958
Hey...! You callin' me a liar?!

303
00:16:26,666 --> 00:16:30,250
[SHIRO] Yep... Hear that?

304
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:33,916
This part wants nothing
to do with being killed.

305
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:42,875
How the hell would
you know what it wants?

306
00:16:42,958 --> 00:16:44,958
We've never even met.

307
00:16:45,041 --> 00:16:47,500
[SHIRO] Yes we have.

308
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:49,000
Oh yeah...?

309
00:16:49,083 --> 00:16:51,625
Then how come
I don't remember you?

310
00:16:51,708 --> 00:16:53,541
Like that really matters.

311
00:16:53,625 --> 00:16:57,666
Ganta and Shiro are
the bestest buddies!

312
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:02,333
Wait a second...
How do you know my name?

313
00:17:04,250 --> 00:17:07,250
If you don't want to
be killed, then cheer up.

314
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:09,125
What does
that even mean?

315
00:17:09,208 --> 00:17:11,000
'Kay, look...
Last I checked,

316
00:17:11,083 --> 00:17:13,166
buddies don't try to bash
each others' skulls in...

317
00:17:13,250 --> 00:17:14,625
Get me?

318
00:17:14,708 --> 00:17:16,750
So you wouldn't
kill your friends...

319
00:17:16,833 --> 00:17:18,375
[GANTA GASPS]

320
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:24,083
Of course I wouldn't!

321
00:17:24,166 --> 00:17:27,375
Not on your life!

322
00:17:27,458 --> 00:17:32,250
I'd never intentionally
hurt the people I care about.

323
00:17:34,833 --> 00:17:36,416
Ow!

324
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:37,666
[PRISONER 1-A]
Do all mass murderers

325
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:39,708
get the four-star
treatment here?

326
00:17:39,791 --> 00:17:41,583
C'mon... Don't
provoke the kid.

327
00:17:41,666 --> 00:17:42,833
I'm just sayin', ditch-digging

328
00:17:42,916 --> 00:17:45,125
doesn't seem like that
much of a punishment.

329
00:17:45,208 --> 00:17:46,750
[PRISONER 1-B]
I don't know, man...

330
00:17:46,833 --> 00:17:50,625
Kid looks more like somebody's
doormat than a ruthless psycho.

331
00:17:50,708 --> 00:17:51,500
Heh...

332
00:17:51,583 --> 00:17:52,750
Use your damn head...

333
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:54,166
If he looked like what he is,

334
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:56,500
he wouldn't have been able
to ice so many people.

335
00:17:56,583 --> 00:17:59,291
Don't get any ideas about your
reputation meaning jack shit

336
00:17:59,375 --> 00:18:01,958
in these parts, schizoid.

337
00:18:02,041 --> 00:18:03,916
Hey... Bet you got a hard-on

338
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,666
when they passed
your sentence...

339
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:07,875
Just like when you smeared
your little friends' guts

340
00:18:07,958 --> 00:18:09,791
all over the wall.

341
00:18:09,875 --> 00:18:12,916
[GANTA THINKING]
It wasn't me... It wasn't me...

342
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,791
Did you do it because
you were picked on?

343
00:18:14,875 --> 00:18:17,083
Did all the popular
chicks ignore you?

344
00:18:17,166 --> 00:18:18,916
C'mon, your secret's
safe with me...

345
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,791
What was it like
killing those kids--

346
00:18:20,875 --> 00:18:21,791
[PRISONER 1-A YELLS]

347
00:18:21,875 --> 00:18:24,541
You're a big meanie!

348
00:18:24,625 --> 00:18:28,083
Ganta would never intentionally
hurt the people he cares about.

349
00:18:28,166 --> 00:18:30,333
You... bitch!

350
00:18:30,416 --> 00:18:32,708
[PRISONER 1-A YELLS]

351
00:18:32,791 --> 00:18:33,333
Woah!

352
00:18:33,416 --> 00:18:34,583
[THUD]

353
00:18:34,666 --> 00:18:36,166
[PRISONER 1-B YELLS]

354
00:18:37,791 --> 00:18:39,583
What in the hell
is her damage?

355
00:18:39,666 --> 00:18:42,208
I thought all the A Block
gimps were on ditch detail.

356
00:18:42,291 --> 00:18:44,958
[GANTA] You bastard!

357
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:47,791
[GANTA YELLS]

358
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:51,708
[PRISONER 1-A] This ain't
a classroom, you little shit.

359
00:18:51,791 --> 00:18:53,208
[GANTA YELLS]

360
00:18:54,958 --> 00:18:59,291
[TAMAKI]
The "man in red" he says...

361
00:18:59,375 --> 00:19:01,416
Few people witness
the Wretched Egg in action

362
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,833
and live to tell about it...

363
00:19:02,916 --> 00:19:04,958
You're extremely fortunate.

364
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:06,833
Unless you're not.

365
00:19:06,916 --> 00:19:09,625
[TAMAKI LAUGHS]

366
00:19:09,708 --> 00:19:12,958
There are two choices
before you right now, boy...

367
00:19:13,041 --> 00:19:16,125
Get kicked into
the dirt and perish...

368
00:19:16,208 --> 00:19:19,458
...or become my
shiny new plaything.

369
00:19:20,041 --> 00:19:21,583
[GANTA] Stop!

370
00:19:21,666 --> 00:19:23,500
You're hurting me!

371
00:19:23,583 --> 00:19:26,500
[GANTA SCREAMS]

372
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:29,625
[GANTA THINKING]
Please... Not like this.

373
00:19:29,708 --> 00:19:30,125
[BEEP]

374
00:19:30,208 --> 00:19:33,708
[EXPLOSION]

375
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:38,375
[METAL CREAKS AND SNAPS]

376
00:19:40,708 --> 00:19:43,333
[GANTA THINKING]
I don't want to die in here.

377
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,583
I want to clear my name.

378
00:19:50,458 --> 00:19:53,333
And him...

379
00:19:53,416 --> 00:19:55,958
I want him to pay for
what he's done to me;

380
00:19:56,041 --> 00:19:58,541
for what he's done
to my friends...

381
00:19:58,625 --> 00:20:01,000
For what he did to Mimi!

382
00:20:02,250 --> 00:20:04,958
I want to live.

383
00:20:05,041 --> 00:20:07,625
I want to live!

384
00:20:07,708 --> 00:20:12,083
[WHOOSHING SOUND]

385
00:20:18,083 --> 00:20:19,916
[ALARM SOUNDS]

386
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,125
[ANNOUNCER MAN]
We have a death row inmate

387
00:20:21,208 --> 00:20:23,500
resisting execution in area D4.

388
00:20:23,583 --> 00:20:27,166
A hostage has been taken.
Immediate backup requested.

389
00:20:27,250 --> 00:20:30,000
[PRISONER 1-D GROANS]

390
00:20:30,083 --> 00:20:30,958
[KASUGA] If you know
what's good for you,

391
00:20:31,041 --> 00:20:32,291
you'll let him
go right now!

392
00:20:32,375 --> 00:20:34,208
Shut your hole!
I need some candy!

393
00:20:34,291 --> 00:20:37,125
Bring me some candy or
I'll slit his throat right now!

394
00:20:37,208 --> 00:20:39,583
Ma'am, the prisioner refusing
to lay down his weapon!

395
00:20:39,666 --> 00:20:42,208
And has the data on
his collar been confirmed?

396
00:20:42,291 --> 00:20:44,166
No ma'am.

397
00:20:45,541 --> 00:20:47,333
Keep him occupied
with small talk...

398
00:20:47,416 --> 00:20:48,833
He doesn't
have too long.

399
00:20:48,916 --> 00:20:50,041
Yes ma'am!

400
00:20:50,125 --> 00:20:52,791
Uh... Hey...

401
00:20:52,875 --> 00:20:54,250
So... All
things considered,

402
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:55,750
it sure is
a nice day out.

403
00:20:55,833 --> 00:20:59,500
Damn it...!
Please... help me!

404
00:20:59,583 --> 00:21:02,000
I don't have any more
cast points left!

405
00:21:02,083 --> 00:21:05,458
I'm begging you...
I need candy...

406
00:21:05,541 --> 00:21:08,250
[RAPID BEEPING]

407
00:21:08,333 --> 00:21:10,791
[PRISONER 1-D YELLS]

408
00:21:16,208 --> 00:21:18,833
[COLLAR RELEASES]

409
00:21:19,541 --> 00:21:23,166
I'm sorry, but the
rules are the rules.

410
00:21:37,166 --> 00:21:38,750
[BEEPING]

411
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:46,416
[PARK ANNOUNCER LADY]
Thank you for visiting

412
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:48,041
Deadman Wonderland.

413
00:21:48,125 --> 00:21:51,041
Come back and
see us again soon.

414
00:21:55,416 --> 00:21:57,916
I'm not dead...?

415
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:02,083
Holy crap... How am
I not dead after that?

416
00:22:09,958 --> 00:22:14,166
Oh no...!
How bad are you hurt?!

417
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:18,083
Wowie... I am so full.

418
00:22:20,041 --> 00:22:22,000
Wake up!

419
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:27,583
Hey you.

420
00:22:27,666 --> 00:22:30,375
Did I say full, 'cause
if it's snack time again...

421
00:22:30,458 --> 00:22:34,416
Will you answer me?!
Are you hurt?

422
00:22:35,708 --> 00:22:37,250
Oh hey!
I've got an idea!

423
00:22:37,333 --> 00:22:39,791
Next time let's eat
our snacks together!

424
00:22:39,875 --> 00:22:40,750
Huh?

425
00:22:40,833 --> 00:22:42,166
Snack time is so much more fun

426
00:22:42,250 --> 00:22:46,708
when you have someone
sweet to share it with.

427
00:22:46,791 --> 00:22:48,750
Yeah sure...

428
00:22:48,833 --> 00:22:51,000
I guess you've got to have
fun whenever you can...

429
00:22:51,083 --> 00:22:53,000
Yup...!

430
00:22:53,083 --> 00:22:57,166
Bestest buddies
forever and ever!

431
00:22:57,250 --> 00:22:59,000
[PARK ANNOUNCER LADY]
Welcome, one and all,

432
00:22:59,083 --> 00:23:02,333
to Deadman Wonderland!

433
00:23:08,250 --> 00:23:13,208
♪ closing song ♪

434
00:24:38,875 --> 00:24:40,166
[MAKINA]
Death row inmates must

435
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:42,708
consume candy once
every three days.

436
00:24:42,791 --> 00:24:44,041
To secure their portion,

437
00:24:44,125 --> 00:24:46,333
they're required to make
a spectacle of themselves,

438
00:24:46,416 --> 00:24:49,958
risking death virtually
every step of the way...

439
00:24:50,041 --> 00:24:52,250
Life's a bitch.

